race.comment: CERTIFIED COPY (1) brought strong relative from to resumption but looked short of a run in much stronger at Eagle Farm. The lightly-raced galloper won his only second-up start easily at Doomben and the 3kg claim takes care of most of the weight rise. Suited and quick improvement is on the cards. BELLZEN (3) ran into a place here second-up and has more to give over the longer sprint. Has the rail and is still well shy of his best. CARDSHARP (4) raced favourite at Lismore first up but lacked a kick after settling well back. He will have to do it the hard way again, but the longer journey suits and his best would see him in the finish. PRIVATE TENDER (6) led and placed at Lismore two back over 1310m, and that form would see him get some of the cash.
